modules.description: Initializes a serialization output buffer and provides methods to serialize primitive types, tuples, variants, and records into a structured binary format. It handles boolean, integer, floating-point, character, and string values, as well as complex data structures with named fields and variant types. Each operation appends data to an output buffer, tracking errors during the serialization process.

Provides functions to serialize and deserialize OCaml values into and from formats like JSON, XML, and binary. Works with arbitrary data types including records, variants, lists, and custom types. Used to convert complex data structures into a transportable form for networking or persistent storage.

Serializes various data types into a binary format, appending values to an output buffer while tracking errors. It supports primitives like booleans, integers, and strings, as well as structured types such as tuples, records, and variants. Operations include writing individual values and nested structures, with explicit control over data layout. For example, it can serialize a record with named fields or a variant with associated data into a compact binary representation.
